      <scopecontent id="aspace_50038b165864927b772538a176cda4db">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The album, probably compiled by John T. Windrim, consists of black and white photographs and postcards documenting the buildings and grounds of Yale University. Included are notes and drawings related to floor plans and a note on the stone used to build Harkness Hall. An announcement for a dinner in honor of architect James H. Windrim is also included.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
